-- Greek Personal Income Tax Total of Budget Rises in 3rd-Qtr
-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a
-- 2012-01-27T12:06:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/greek-personal-income-tax-total-of-budget-rises-in-3rd-qtr.html
Greece ’s revenue from personal
taxation accounted for 20 percent of the country’s total budget
income in the third-quarter of 2011, according to the Hellenic
Statistical Authority.  Contributions to the state from personal income rose from
18.5 percent a year earlier, according to an e-mailed statement
from the Athens-based statistical bureau.  Total revenue from personal income taxes reached 4.4
billion euros ($5.8 billion) for the quarter of a total of 22
billion euros, the agency reported.  -- Editors: Chris Peterson, James Kraus  To contact the reporter on this story:
